  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is posting links to your website allowed on Quora?",
  "response": "Posting links to your website on Quora is allowed, but there are some important guidelines and best practices to follow:\n\n1. **Relevance**: The link should be relevant to the question being asked. It should provide additional information or context that helps answer the question.\n\n2. **Disclosure**: If you have a financial or personal interest in the website you're linking to, you should disclose this. For example, if it's your own website or business, you should mention that.\n\n3. **Quality**: The content on the linked page should be of high quality and provide value to the reader. Low-quality or spammy content can lead to your answer being downvoted or removed.\n\n4. **Moderation**: Quora has strict moderation policies. If your answer is seen as primarily self-promotional or spam, it may be removed, and your account could be at risk of suspension.\n\n5. **Quantity**: Don't overdo it. If every answer you provide contains a link to your website, it will likely be flagged as spam.\n\n6. **Value First**: Always prioritize providing a helpful answer. The link should be supplementary to your answer, not the main focus.\n\nHere's an example of how you might include a link in a way that follows these guidelines:\n\n\"If you're looking for more information on this topic, I've written a detailed guide on [Your Website Name] that covers it in-depth. You can find it here: [link to your website]. Full disclosure, this is my personal website where I share insights on [topic].\"\n\nRemember, the key is to be helpful and transparent. If you're providing valuable information and not just trying to promote your site, you're more likely to stay within Quora's guidelines.",
